aVOur first tapir program
p105
aVtook place in the Atlantic Forest
p106
aVin the eastern part of Brazil,
p107
aVone of the most threatened biomes in the world.
p108
aVThe destruction of the Atlantic Forest
p109
aVbegan in the early 1500s,
p110
aVwhen the Portuguese first arrived in Brazil,
p111
aVbeginning European colonization in the eastern part of South America.
p112
aVThis forest was almost completely cleared
p113
aVfor timber, agriculture, cattle ranching and the construction of cities,
p114
aVand today only seven percent of the Atlantic forest
p115
aVis still left standing.
