aVAnd tapirs are found in very, very small, isolated, disconnected populations.
p117
aVIn the Atlantic Forest, we found out that tapirs move through open areas
p118
aVof pastureland and agriculture
p119
aVgoing from one patch of forest to patch of forest.
p120
aVSo our main approach in this region
p121
aVwas to use our tapir data to identify the potential places
p122
aVfor the establishment of wildlife corridors
p123
aVin between those patches of forest,
p124
aVreconnecting the habitat
p125
aVso that tapirs and many other animals could cross the landscape safely.
